captions.text: [MUSIC - KATIE SKY, "ONLY YOU"]
-Hey guys.
It's Brooklyn and Bailey.

And obviously, today we are
doing our (BOTH) P.O. Box Haul.
We're super excited.

This sign was made
by Emma from Arizona.
-Mm-hm.

-(BOTH) And it's adorable, so
we had to use it for our intro.

But I'm just going to
let you all know now,

we're going to be like speed
talking like little chipmunks,

because we have a ton
of stuff to cover.

-Over 200 things were sent
from all over the world.

-From India, Australia,
France, Paris, Asia.
-Crazy places.
-Everywhere.

We had people with
dyslexia, people with--
-Cystic fibrosis.

-Yeah, we had people, twins,
triplets, guys, (BOTH)
20-year-olds.
It was amazing.

We loved hearing
all of your stories

about your dogs, your
loved ones, your families,
your channels.
-Pets.
-Your hobbies.
-Birds, a bunch of cool stuff.
-Your school.
-School projects.

-Obviously, we could
only pick a few things

to show in our video, so we have
a couple things laid out for us

to show you guys
that caught our eye.
So we will get started.

-You guys are probably wondering
why we are wearing all of this.

But holy rainbow
looms are totally in.
-Holy cow.
-We got like 50 hundred of them.
-We have like 5000 bajillion.

-And we them all, colorful
beautiful rainbow looms.

-We're wearing all
of them right now.
-Yes, we are.
So thank you all.

There were so many we
could not name all of you.

But thank you all for the
rainbow looms, including

all of this new
jewelry, as well.
We have so much jewelry.

We are set for the next
couple fashion videos.
-[LAUGHS] My gosh.

-I'm pretty sure we have
enough jewelry to make us--
-We have like charms.
-And hair bows included in that.
-Yes.

-I mean, people, you
guys are craftsy.
You can make hair bows.
I mean, come on.
-Yeah, but--

-These all look
pretty dang good.

-Thank you for all of the
jewelry you guys sent us.
-Yes, thank you.

We have these amazing little
Brooklyn and Bailey rainbow
loom dolls from--
-They're so cute.
---Elise.
She is from--
-Washington?
-Washington, yes.
-Yes.
-And she sent us these.

-And then we have
these hair bows

from Angie, who has a
website called NeverNola.com.

She makes these hair bows,
and we use these all the time.

So when she saw us
doing a P.O. Box Haul,

she just sent us
some more, so we
could mention them in our video.
-Yeah.
-These are adorable.
-They're super cute.

-So if you want any
headbands, go to her website.

-Next up, we have some
of our food favorites.
-Mm-hm.

-These suckers are
from Priscilla.

She took some pictures
off of Instagram

and actually put them in
the suckers with our names
around them.
-They're so cool.

-And they're edible,
and they're super cute.
So we really love those.
And thank you, Priscilla.
-Mm-hm.

-This is Vegemite
from Australia.

It is the Australian
peanut butter.

Abby from Australia
sent this to us.

And we had our
whole family try it.
And it was very flavorful.
-Very flavorful.

-Very different from the
American peanut butter.

-We enjoyed having
you send us some us
some of your native candies.
-Yeah.

-Because we would love
trying new foods, so.
-Because we love trying them.
It was super cool.
-Mm-hm.

-And next up, we have
Stroopwafels from Nicole
and Clarice--
-Stroopwafels.
--in the Netherlands.

And we love
Stroopwafels so much.
-Mm-hm.

-We've been waiting
for this video,

so we can just eat them after.
[LAUGHS] But we love them.
And thank you guys so much.
-Mm-hm.

Next I have a girl name Nadia
sent us $5, which of course, we

don't need anyone to
send us their money.
But they were all--
-It was super sweet.

-Yeah, this girl specifically
mentioned giving us the $5

to go and buy ourselves some
Reese's, because she didn't

want to send them
through the mail.
So thank you for the $5.

We will definitely go
get Reese's, because I
can't complain about Reese's.

And speaking of
Reese's, a girl named

Lily sent us a few packages
of Reese's, and you all
know how much we love these.
-Mm-hm.

-So thank you,
Lily, for the candy.

-Next up, we have
this Lion Bar, which
is from Rachel from the UK.
-Mm-hm.

-And my mom has
already eaten it.
And we got to try some.

She studied abroad in Israel,
and it was her favorite candy
bar.

So as soon as she saw that,
she freaked out, and made us
all try it.
-She like, cuts it.
And she made us all try it.

-Yeah, it was super good, so
thank you for the Lion bar.

-Next we have a
Canadian chocolate bar.

It was sent by a girl
named Alexia from Canada.

And I've never actually
tried chocolate from Canada.

So I'm super excited to
open this up and try it.
-Yes.

-So thank you, Alexia, for
sending us this chocolate bar.

Next, we have some art
stuff that we picked out.

First, we have a CGH
canvas made by Mary Jane.

It's adorable, really
good at painting.

I could never do
anything Ike that.
-Seriously.

-But thank you, Mary Jane
for sending this to us.
It's adorable.

Next, we have this
amazing newspaper collage.
They, like, did our face.
It by Hannah from Georgia.

And she took like
little newspaper clips
and like created our face.

And it even matches
our room, so I

think we're going to
hang it up in our room,
because this is like amazing.
-It's really crazy craft.

-I don't even know how long
this took her, but it's amazing.

-It was probably-- it was for
a school project, wasn't it?

-Yeah, I think it might have
been from a school project.

And she even had like
a little hidden Mickey
inside my glasses.

Like, this entire thing
is just so creative.
-It's so cute.
-So thank you, Hannah.

We might hang this
up in our room.

-This is from [? Kerula ?]
from Michigan.

And she sent in this little
snow globe looking thing.

And it has all of the initials
of everyone in our family.
-Mm-hm.
And this little snow globe--
-Yeah.

--is all made out
of clay and stuff.
So it is adorable.

-We thought that was
super crafty and adorable.
-Mm-hm.
-And this is from Allison.

And she water-colored this
little painting over here.
-Let's go see it.
-Amazing.

-And then she had her
grandpa craft this little--
-Ah, what's it called?
---canvas holder thingy.
-The canvas holder.
-I'm not artsy.

I don't know the names
of all the stuff.

But this little
picture holder thingy.

And we thought that was
so cute and creative,
so we put that one in here, too.
-Mm-hm.

-Next up we have some of
the drawings people sent us.
-Mm-hm.

-This one's is a
little quilt that

says life is about how to
create your awesome self.

It's a little
quote from Genesis.
-Adorable.

-And we thought it was
super cute, so we have that.
-Mm-hm.

I have this cartoon
picture, which amazing.
-Seriously.

-I don't even know
how to draw cartoon.

And it's from this
girl, named Mia.

So thank you, Mia, for drawing
us in our cartoon selves.

And then I have
this picture of us

from one of our book reviews
with Divergent and Delirium.
-In this studio.
-And Annie drew it.
Thank you, Annie.

I thought it was adorable,
because it just kind of like
caught us in like our--
-Element.

our little element,
like, our videos.
So it was adorable.

And last but not least,
we have this letter
written by a girl named Lily.

And she just drew pictures
of like Brady, our dog.
-And some like CGH.
-And sunglasses and CGH.

And like some nail
polish in there.

-And she has a bunch
of cute little drawings
on the side of her notes.

So we thought those
were super cute.
-Colorful and creative.
-And colorful, so.
-So it's adorable.
-Yeah.

-Now, we're going to show you
some of the cutest packaging
that we found.

First off, we have this
cute little letter.

They're just drawn in
like rainbow colors.
We thought it was adorable.

It's from this
girl named Valerie.

So thank you for sending
this adorable packaging
on this envelope, Valerie.

-Next up, we have this one
from Savannah from Ohio.

And we thought it was super
cute, because it had just

like a bunch of like
lines of designs,

and it was very interesting
when I opened it.
So I really liked it.

-This manila folder
made us all crack up.

It says, hey, open us
in your video, please.

-And we used it in a
picture in Instagram, too.
-Yes.

This is from Tinsley and Micah,
so thank you for making us
all laugh, Tinsley and Micah.

-We have this envelope
from Stephanie,

and it's got puzzle pieces on
the front and this cute little
rainbow splatter on the back.

And we thought it was
so cute and creative.
-Mm-hm.

-So thank you, Stephanie,
for sending us this envelope.

-Now, we are going
to show you guys

some of the letters that
caught our attention.

First off, I have this letter
from a girl named Blair.

Well, not really a
girl, more of a woman,
because she's 20 years old.

And we just read your
entire letter, Blair.

It was so wonderful to find out
that people older than us still
enjoy our videos.

It was super
touching, and we're so
glad you sent us this letter.

And we'd love to
hear from you again.
-Yes.

And we got This letter
from Tai and Jack,
who are 15-year-old twins.
And they sent us this letter.

And they're boys,
mind you, boys.

And they said they liked
to watch our videos,

because they thought
we were cute,
which was very flattering.

-So we were wondering,
Tai and Jack,

if you guys would come
to our meet up in Dallas?

-If we had one in Dallas,
if you guys would come?
So please tell us that.

And we thought this letter
was very interesting.

So thank you, guys,
for sending it to us.

And thanks for being guys
who watch our videos.
-Mm-hm.

Other notable are some
recipes, cookie recipes

that a girl named
Michaela sent us.

So we're definitely
going to try these out.
-Yes.

-We also had two girls named
Ava and Sharon, who sent us

a ton of pictures of
all their-- what is it?
What is the word for it?

All of their pictures
of when they tried out
all or our DIYs and hairstyles.
-Which was super cute.
-So we loved seeing these.

And the longest
letter award goes

to a girl named
Divia from India.
We read your entire letter.
Thank you for your kind words.
-It was super sweet.
-Mm-hm.

-And we just wanted
to mention Scout.

We absolutely loved
the saying on your card
that said braider in training.
That gave us a good laugh.
-That was adorable.

-We got all of these gifts
from Julia from California.
And she was super sweet.

She sent every single person
in our family something.
-Mm-hm.
-And we just loved them.

She even got Brady a little,
like a squeaky toy, little bone
thing.
-So cute.

-And we also thought, Julia, you
had the prettiest handwriting.

-Oh my gosh, yes,
it's beautiful.

-So I think you won the
prettiest handwriting.

We were just obsessing
over oh, how pretty it was.

-Yeah, so I have this quote
block sent by Kate and Grace,

and its in remembrance
of their friend, Joseph,

who passed away of
heart complications.

And we can really
appreciate that,

because of our little
sister Paisley also
has heart complications.

So you're supposed
to take a picture

while doing a circus
act with this block.

So we really appreciated
that and wanted
to mention that in our video.

We also have this
rec it journal,

which I don't know if you
all know what that is.

But it's basically
like a journal

where you do like a certain
thing for every page.

And our little sister Camry
really, really, really
wants this journal.
-She want to like steal it.
-She's always wanted one.
-So we might give it to Camry.
I don't know.

But thank you, Lily, for sending
us this wonderful journal.

Last but very much not
least, we have this owl bag

from this girl named Lars
from the Netherlands.
-And it's super cute.
-It's Super duper cute.
-We love it.
-So thank you so much.

-And thank you all to
everyone who sent us.
You cannot thank you enough.

Even the post office thought
it was crazy cool how much--
-Hugs.
---mail we were getting.

So thank you to everyone
who sent us something.
-Thank you, thank you.
-We really appreciate it.
-Mm-hm.

Don't forget to leave a comment
below on what you guys liked

the best about this video,
like whether it's the stuff,

or us talking, or even
sending the stuff.
Just let us know.
And--

-There will be a list at the
end of the video of everyone
who sent us something.
-Mm-hm.

-So if you want to see your
name or something on there,
go check it out.

-Don't forget to like,
favorite, and subscribe.

And I'm pretty sure that's all
we have for you guys today.

So we will see you
guys next week.
-Bye.
-Bye.
-Love you.
[MUSIC - KATIE SKY, "ONLY YOU"]

-Thought I can end
fancy, so let's get

this-- oh, yep, huge wing
I got right, right there.
[MUSIC - KATIE SKY, "ONLY YOU"]
